message: APRA is not a right-wing party. Insisting on categorizing it as such contradicts all sources possible pertaining the program and how it is currently a member of the Socialist International. Stop.

/* Move to the right */ Bustamante y Rivero was not an ultra-conservative, rather a centre-leftist. He was a lawyer elected under the FDN in order to counter the conservative UR (defeating them in 1945). FDN was composed of APRA, the Communist Party, and independent intellectuals. The sources that are cited are wrong and at the same time, APRA is not a right-wing party. It is a pragmatic [[Third Way]] centre-left party. It's like saying Tony Blair was "right-wing".
